This topic describes how to install and configure the Aerospike Service Broker for PCF.

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure the Aerospike Service Broker

To install and configure the Aerospike Service Broker tile, perform the following steps:

1. Download the product file from Pivotal Network.

1. Upload the product file on the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard.

1. Click **Add** next to the uploaded Aerospike Service Broker for PCF tile in the Ops Manager **Available Products** view to add it to your staging area.

1. Click the newly added **Aerospike Service Broker for PCF** tile.

1. Put the hostname or IP address of one of the nodes of your Aerospike cluster into the **Aerospike DB Host** field.

1. Ensure the port number in the **Aerospike DB Port** field is correct. This should match the **service port** as configured on the Aerospike database.

1. Select the appropriate **Aerospike License Type**, **Community** or **Enterprise**.

1. In the **Aerospike Admin Namespace** field, enter the namespace that the Aerospike Service Broker will use to store service and application bindings.

1. If you have deployed the Enterprise Edition of the Aerospike database server, enter the **User** and **Password** for the account information that the Service Broker will use to access the Aerospike database.

1. Click **Save**.

1. Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Apply Changes** to install the Aerospike Service Broker for PCF tile.

